-- Russia unlikely to introduce capital controls in near future - VTB CEO
-- 
-- Wed Oct 01, 2014 02:56AM EDT
-- None



MOSCOW, Oct 1 (Reuters) - The introduction of capital controls in Russia cannot be ruled out, but the measure is unlikely to be introduced any time soon, Andrei Kostin, chief executive officer of Russia's state-controlled VTB Bank <VTBR.MM>, said on Wednesday.

